Usage: metagen [options]

Options:
  --version   show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help  show this help message and exit
  -H HERD     Name of herd. If not specified, It will be empty. This requires
              either the -e or -m option.
  -e EMAIL    Maintainer's email address
  -n NAME     Maintainer's name
  -m          Use name and email address from ECHANGELOG_USER environmental
              variable. This is a shortcut for -e <email> -n <name>
  -d DESC     Description of maintainership
  -l LONG     Long description of package.
  -o OUTPUT   Specify location of output file.
  -f          Force overwrite of existing metadata.
  -v          Verbose. Output of file to stdout. (default)
  -q          Squelch output of file to stdout.
  -Q          Do not write file to disk.
